{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01D8XgVzB14sxgpsokuosU12","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to enable the shovel plugin. The enabled_plugins file is mounted from a ConfigMap. I need to:\n1. Update the ConfigMap to include the shovel plugin\n2. Restart the RabbitMQ pods (or find another way)\n\nHowever, restarting the pods would interrupt service. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, with a 3-node cluster, I can do a rolling restart - update the ConfigMap, then restart one pod at a time. The cluster will remain available during a rolling restart.\n\nLet me:\n1. Update the ConfigMap for blue to add shovel plugins\n2. Do a rolling restart of the blue cluster pods\n3. Then configure the shovel to move messages from blue to green\n\nThe messages in the queue will persist on disk during the restart, so that's fine.\n\nActually, I'm reconsidering whether I need the shovel plugin at all. I could use the RabbitMQ Management HTTP API instead - create a job that consumes messages from the blue cluster and republishes them to green. This avoids the plugin enable and restart entirely.\n\nI could use rabbitmqadmin or just curl to consume and republish messages between clusters. Let me explore this simpler approach that doesn't require any restarts.\n\nI'm thinking through the tradeoffs: the shovel plugin is the most native RabbitMQ approach and handles ordering correctly, but it requires a pod restart. The Management API approach with curl in a job is simpler operationally - I can use the existing curl-test pod that's already running in the namespace to run a migration script that gets messages from blue and republishes them to green in batches.\n\nLet me go with the shovel approach since it's the cleanest native solution, but first I need to verify whether the queues are actually durable so messages won't be lost during the rolling restart.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":763,"cache_read_input_tokens":34136,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":763},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5d068a7d-e547-4349-8c1d-ec658aa1d2bc","uuid":"38d2ed30-e4a9-49be-b376-f28a6818375d","request_id":"req_011CcPxe4oRjZnACxCfvMruB"}
