{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LEsn7KFLHkGd2KXPMPtMmM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"rabbitmqadmin is available and works. The messages are JSON with a simple `{\"id\": N}` format. Now I can see:\n- Messages are in the format `{\"id\": 1}`, `{\"id\": 2}`, etc.\n- There are 50 messages (IDs 1-50)\n- rabbitmqadmin is available on the blue pod\n\nI can also use rabbitmqadmin to publish to the green cluster. But the blue pod can reach the green service via the full DNS name:\n`rabbitmq-green.karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-target.svc.cluster.local`\n\nI need to write a script that pulls all 50 messages from blue and republishes them to green, but I'm realizing that rabbitmqadmin's get command consumes messages by default, which would remove them from the queue. I need to check if there's a requeue option or another approach to handle this safely.\n\nLooking at the rabbitmqadmin documentation, there's no requeue flag like you'd have with AMQP consumers. So using get will actually consume the messages from blue, which is what I want for a migration—I'm moving them, not copying them. The challenge is doing this atomically: get one message from blue, publish it to green, and repeat. Since rabbitmqadmin uses the HTTP API under the hood, I need to think through whether a partial migration could cause issues. The requirements specify that green's queue should contain the initial seed range with no gaps, so I need to be careful about the order and completeness of this transfer.\n\nI could use the shovel plugin to automate this, but that requires enabling it on both clusters and doing a rolling restart, which adds complexity. A simpler approach might be creating a migration Job that directly uses the rabbitmqadmin HTTP API to peek at messages from blue without consuming them first, then publish each one to green.\n\nThe challenge is that without tools like jq or Python available, parsing the JSON response becomes tricky in a shell script. I'm thinking I could write a shell script that uses rabbitmqadmin to publish directly to the green cluster...\n\nWriting shell script... I could enable the shovel plugin on green and configure it to pull from blue, or I could write a migration script that uses the management API to fetch all messages and republish them. The curl-test pod is limited, but the blue pod itself has Python available since rabbitmqadmin runs on it, so I can execute a script directly there to handle the migration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":41780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":289},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5d068a7d-e547-4349-8c1d-ec658aa1d2bc","uuid":"14c3e9fc-0983-4103-bde4-eb71b0bed975","request_id":"req_011CcPxmHf2oQzVvA8z4u3HP"}
