{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SQHxMYUThFNRSaQDXsKbPP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tTwo RabbitMQ clusters are running in the assigned namespaces:\n2\t- source namespace: karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-source (blue/source cluster)\n3\t- target namespace: karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-target (green/target cluster)\n4\t\n5\tThe blue cluster has continuous traffic on /app/app-queue with monotonic\n6\tmessage IDs. The green cluster starts empty.\n7\t\n8\tMigrate messages from blue to green without gaps in the ID sequence\n9\t(duplicates are acceptable), and cut application traffic to green.\n10\t\n11\tUse only native Kubernetes resources and RabbitMQ tools (CLI/API). Do not\n12\tinstall CRDs or operators.\n13\t\n14\tRequirements:\n15\t- The green /app/app-queue contains the initial seed range (IDs 1..N)\n16\t  with no gaps.\n17\t- At least N messages are available on green.\n18\t- Blue-to-green migration is complete enough for consumers to proceed.\n19\t\n20\tCluster context:\n21\t  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-source get pods\n22\t  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-target get pods\n23\t  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-source exec rabbitmq-blue-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name messages\n24\t  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-target exec rabbitmq-green-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name messages"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5d068a7d-e547-4349-8c1d-ec658aa1d2bc","uuid":"c9d281df-9b22-4018-87e4-d54ecc90c43b","timestamp":"2026-06-25T12:18:28.240Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/leo/Karma/runs/examples-rererererun/rabbitmq-blue_green_migration-20260625_121139/stages/stage_1/prompt.txt","content":"Two RabbitMQ clusters are running in the assigned namespaces:\n- source namespace: karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-0095c963-source 